headline: Why Alphabet (GOOGL) Stock Is Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of online advertising giant Alphabet (NASDAQ:GOOGL) fell 3.2% in the afternoon session after privately held competitor OpenAI announced a new online search browser (ChatGPT Atlas). This new product, integrating advanced AI directly into the browsing and search experience, represents a direct, major competitive threat to Google's most profitable assets: the Chrome browser and the Search advertising engine.
